  <properties>
    <property name="family">Access Control Controller</property>
    <property name="variant">Red 4 Expander</property>
    <property name="part number">R4E</property>
    <property name="dimensions">Red Max 1:1 calibrated 3.0518 in x 2.7302 in</property>
    <property name="terminal pitch assumption">5.08 mm</property>
    <property name="mounting pattern">Lower narrow Red Max slot</property>
    <property name="mounting hole spacing">1.8512 in x 1.9002 in</property>
    <property name="calibration source">Red Max exact 1368 x 1752 px image at 96 DPI</property>
    <property name="SVG coordinate density">72 units per inch</property>
    <property name="renderer compatibility">Plain default SVG namespace; no generated ns0 prefixes</property>
  </properties>
  <description>PDK Red 4 Expander four-door access-control controller. Estimated board size is 5.61 x 5.30 inches, calculated from the repeated terminal spacing in the manufacturer artwork using an assumed 5.08 mm terminal pitch. Includes four OSDP two-pin jumper headers and four relay wet/dry jumper headers. This custom part is intended for wiring diagrams and system documentation only. Mounting-hole positions and PCB geometry are not verified. Recalibrated against the exact 1368 x 1752 px, 96 DPI Red Max enclosure artwork. Target pattern: Lower narrow Red Max slot; mounting-hole spacing 1.8512 x 1.9002 inches. Resulting breadboard footprint: 3.0518 x 2.7302 inches. This revision removes generated namespace prefixes that can break Qt/Fritzing SVG rendering and normalizes every SVG view to 72 coordinate units per physical inch, matching established Fritzing part conventions.</description>
